<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4614132>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIG. 18. Seasonally flooded forest (várzea) at Seringal Condor, on the left bank of the Rio Juruá, Amazonas state, Brazil (appendix 1: locality 25; photo by J.L. Patton). Sparse understory vegetation characterizes some várzea sites like this one, but dense stands of giant herbs such as Heliconia spp. (Heliconiaceae) and Costa spp. (Costaceae) can be common elsewhere (Prance, 1979)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4614132/files/figure.png" .

